android.car.os

类 CarPerformanceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.car.CarManagerBase
      • android.car.os.CarPerformanceManager

  • public final class CarPerformanceManager
extends CarManagerBase
    CarPerformanceManager allows applications to tweak performance settings for their processes/threads and listen for CPU available change notifications.

      • onCarDisconnected

        public void onCarDisconnected()
        从类复制的说明: CarManagerBase
        Handle disconnection of car service (=crash). As car service has crashed already, this call should only clean up any listeners / callbacks passed from client. Clearing object passed to car service is not necessary as car service has crashed. Note that Car*Manager will not work any more as all binders are invalid. Client should re-create all Car*Managers when car service is restarted.
        指定者:
        onCarDisconnected 在类中 CarManagerBase

      • setThreadPriority

        public void setThreadPriority(ThreadPolicyWithPriority policyWithPriority)
                       throws CarPerformanceManager.SetSchedulerFailedException
        Sets the thread scheduling policy with priority for the current thread. For ThreadPolicyWithPriority.SCHED_DEFAULT scheduling algorithm, the standard round-robin time-sharing algorithm will be used and the priority field will be ignored. Please use Process#setThreadPriority to adjust the priority for the default scheduling.
        参数:
        policyWithPriority - A thread scheduling policy with priority.
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the policy is not supported or the priority is not within ThreadPolicyWithPriority.PRIORITY_MIN and ThreadPolicyWithPriority.PRIORITY_MAX.
        CarPerformanceManager.SetSchedulerFailedException - If failed to set the scheduling policy and priority.
        java.lang.SecurityException - If permission check failed.

      • getThreadPriority

        public ThreadPolicyWithPriority getThreadPriority()
        Gets the thread scheduling policy with priority for the current thread. For ThreadPolicyWithPriority.SCHED_FIFO or ThreadPolicyWithPriority.SCHED_RR, this function returns the priority for the scheduling algorithm. For ThreadPolicyWithPriority.SCHED_DEFAULT which is the standard round-robin time-sharing algorithm, this function always return 0 for priority. The priority for the default algorithm can be fetched by Process#getThreadPriority.
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If failed to get policy or priority.
        java.lang.SecurityException - If permission check failed.
